  </info>
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>lowdisc_new</refname>
    <refpurpose>  Creates and returns a new sequence. </refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>
    <synopsis>newrng = lowdisc_new()</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
      This command returns a token associated with a new sequence.
      This token can be used later for refering to the associated object.
    </para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Examples</title>
    In the following example, we create a 
    object and immediately destroys it. One finally clears the variable
    which holds the object.
    <programlisting role="example">
      rng = lowdisc_new();
      rng = lowdisc_destroy(rng);
      clear rng;
    </programlisting>
  </refsection>
